We  shared the code,  and the  simulated and 80% -sampled PM 2.5 datasets in the python  package, resautonet  (https://github.com/lspatial/resautonet ).

We obtained the 2015 original images of daily 1 - km res olution AOD with massive missing values from  ftp://dataportal.nccs.nasa.gov/DataRelease  (mean proportion of missing values for all the images: 58%).

We obtained the daily averages over the hourly meteorological  data from China Meteorological Data  Service Center  (http://data.cma.cn/en ) and also imputed for missing values using these monitoring data plus Reanalysis Data from  Modern -Era Retrospective Analysis Version 2.0 (MERRA2 , https://gmao.gsfc.nasa.gov/reanalysis/MERRA -2).

For spatiotemporal surface estimation  of 2015  daily PM 2.5 (unit: μg/m3; spatial resolution : 1 km) , we obtained daily PM 2.5  concentrations  by averaging the observed  hourly monitoring data  from 92 monitoring stations ( http://beijingair.sinaapp.com/ )  (Supplementary Fig.

The regressors  are publicly  available data that include observed and imputed MAIAC  AOD aforementioned, the meteorological parameters ( the same data as those used in the imputation of MAIAC AOD), MERRA2  AOD, mont hly NDVI from the MODIS MODND1D dataset  (http://gscloud.cn ), elevation, coordinates ( x, y, x2, y2, xy).
